## ‚öôÔ∏è Hands-On / Practical Projects

Especially as someone moving into a new platform, nothing beats experience:

### ‚úî Set Up a Crunchy Bridge Test Cluster

* Deploy a basic instance in AWS/Azure/GCP.
* Connect with your usual tooling (`psql`, DBeaver, etc.).
* Practice migrations from a local Postgres instance onto Bridge.
* Experiment with backups, PITR, read replicas, scaling.

### ‚úî Build Performance Scenarios

Use tools like:

* `pgbench` for benchmarking
* `EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, BUFFERS)` for query performance inspection
* pg_stat views to understand workload behaviour

These general Postgres skills pay dividends across any managed Postgres platform.

